Maibelle: Ornate Boxfish (Aracana ornata) Mai's host profile immediately screams fun! And, in my opinion, the boxfish is the most fun fish in the sea! 5:33 PM
Sunder: Mako Shark (Isurus oxyrinchus) Sunder's a lad who keeps moving and there's a common idea that sharks need to always keep moving or else they'll drown. This is true for some sharks (others like nurse sharks can just laze around all they want) but for the shark I selected for Sunder it is true. The mako shark is also the fastest known species of shark which can attain bursts of speed of up to 46 mph (according to Smithsonian Ocean) which I think matches Sunder's athleticism and desire to keep moving forward.
Cetus 3/13/2024 5:45 PM
Han: Reef Manta Ray (Mobula alfredi) Now, Han didn't put much to work with honestly. But what stuck out to me most was the part where he was a hospice nurse. Someone who cares for people near the end of their lives. For this one, there was no other choice... The manta ray. The manta ray is associated with tranquility and serenity. They glide so effortlessly through the water it's as if they're flying. I would know because I've seen them up close before. They might be one of the world's most majestic animals. I can't find any specific, concrete stories about manta rays but I do think they have cultural significance in Polynesian cultures as spirit animals. Most notably, Moana's depiction of the manta ray was in reference to the Aumakua, which Hawaiins believed were deceased family members who would take on the form of a sort of spirit animal like a shark, octopus, or bird to watch over them. (edited)
Cetus 3/13/2024 5:56 PM
Mamo: Common Remora (Remora remora) I TRIED SO HARD TO GET AN ALWAYS SUNNY REFERENCE IN HERE. I knew nothing about the show, but there was an episode tha ttook place in a fish factory. Unfortunately, I could not identify the fish species at all and there was nothing on it online. So, plan B... Remora. Mamo mentioned something about going on vacations a lot (and freeloading), so I thought the remora's like perfect for that. The remora is an annoying little shit that likes to use a modified dorsal fin to attach itself to larger animals like sharks or rays for protection. It's a commensal relationship because the remora doesn't really harm the host but the host doesn't really benefit from the remora. So... There... Mamo, I'm calling you a freeloader thank you.

Dicy: West Atlantic Trumpetfish (Aulostomus maculatus) Oh, boy! This one's gonna be fun. So, I've played Outlaster with Dicy before and something I've noticed is that he likes to backstab people a lot. Being a little sneaky lad and striking when people least expect it. So, I introduce to you the West Atlantic trumpetfish. These guys are highly carnivorous, stealthy predators who use their unique body to help them hunt prey. They'll employ different tactics like hovering motionless among the reef to hide in plain sight, or even swim alongside larger fish as a sort of 'shadowing' behavior which lets them get close to unsuspecting prey. I chose the West Atlantic trumpetfish in particular because its distribution is just the closest to Kentucky as I could possibly get. (edited)

Final Day:
Cetus 3/29/2024 2:28 PM
I wish I could be more celebratory and not mopy y'know. It's just realizing the extent at which Maple has outplayed you, realizing just how all of this had been for nothing, and the feeling of being utterly incapable just... Yeah. I would like to preface that I'm happy for Maple and my misery is not any of his fault or anyone's. Yeah, I'm miserable, oh boo hoo. I literally spent a week in Hawai'i how tragic. It's just I took this thing to such an absurdly, unhealthily serious extent and for it to all be over right at the end. I played the hardest out of anyone here, but playing the hardest doesn't mean you played the best and I didn't play the best. I made strategic blunders that cost me the game and I couldn't fully take out Hayple in the end which... Yeah. It's like the second part of the F4 comp where I just couldn't break it no matter how hard I tried, even if I knew I was losing. It does genuinely feel like a SmORGon 22 situation where I'm in FTC with Bui. Like... There's no real option. Everything is just formality for the most obvious vote of the season. I guess now I'll just... Let it happen because there's nothing I can do to change it. I made my own mistakes and I'm suffering for them. I just don't know if or when I'll be able to play an ORG again because I want to win SO badly. I want to win an ORG that I actually respect a lot like the SmORGon series and I was this close to doing so. But no... My own strategic failures brought me down. I don't know how I could've done better. I want to say maybe if the ORG took place at a better time, but that just feels like a shitty excuse for shitty gameplay. Again, it stings that I'm going into a losing FTC rather than being eliminated for being a threat. Considering Pie and Maple BOTH extended FTC deals to me, it really just shows I was a goat all along and god... God, that hurts. Not even a goat, a goat that thought they were hot shit.
2:34 PM
Again, I won't blame anyone... Maple deserves the win and I'm the only one to blame for having played this badly. It's just, I think this is the one loss that'll be FELT. Like... The one that stings the most. Like Smig Smother, I could've won that if maybe some end game comps went my way. SmORGon 22, I was never winning but I was new and just getting into the scene. And Swur Chronicles, I was actually in a pretty ok spot until the double. But here this'll feel like the one that got away, except now I realized I never had a chance of getting it in the first place. This ORG had many special things it introduced to me like Benno, and I wanted to win a turbulent, exciting ORG full of vote splits and everything because then that's more exciting. That's the white whale. I want to win an ORG that genuinely feels like a tug of war and not one that's a clean domination. The mix of factors going into making an ORG like that are mostly random so idk... But, yeah, this loss'll be one I'll feel for a bit. And fuck man... It is a stupid Discord game, but god damn it I do this with everything. My own writing, my own art, my own grades. It's just this one IS a competition and naturally you're going to be compared to others. It's literally how it functions. And unfortunately, there's no prize for second place or just doing a "good job". It's really a winner takes all and I'm not that winner. (edited)
